reviews.subject: Computer Science
reviews.review: Dr. Smith is an excellent professor who explains complex topics clearly. Highly recommend his classes.

reviews.subject: Mathematics
reviews.review: Dr. Johnson's lectures are thorough, but sometimes the pace is too fast. Overall, a good learning experience.

reviews.subject: Physics
reviews.review: Dr. Brown knows his subject well but lacks engagement with students. His exams are tough.

reviews.subject: Biology
reviews.review: Dr. Lee is passionate about biology and it shows in her teaching. The labs were particularly fun.

reviews.subject: Chemistry
reviews.review: Good professor, but the coursework is challenging. You need to put in a lot of effort to succeed.

reviews.subject: Psychology
reviews.review: Dr. Martinez is incredibly knowledgeable and her classes are very engaging. I learned a lot.

reviews.subject: Economics
reviews.review: Dr. Hernandez's lectures are a bit monotonous and hard to follow. The material is interesting, but the delivery could be better.

reviews.subject: Philosophy
reviews.review: Dr. Wilson challenges you to think deeply about the subject matter. Her grading is fair but tough.

reviews.subject: Sociology
reviews.review: Dr. Clark's classes are informative, but the lectures can drag on. He is approachable for questions though.

reviews.subject: History
reviews.review: Dr. Rodriguez brings history to life with her engaging lectures. A must-take class for history buffs.

reviews.subject: Political Science
reviews.review: Dr. Lewis provides a balanced view on political issues. His classes are informative, but be prepared for heavy reading.

reviews.subject: English Literature
reviews.review: Dr. Walker is knowledgeable but her grading is strict. The workload is heavy, but the material is interesting.

reviews.subject: Anthropology
reviews.review: Dr. Hall's enthusiasm for anthropology is contagious. His classes are well-structured and engaging.

reviews.subject: Art History
reviews.review: Dr. Young's lectures are visually rich and informative. The course requires a lot of memorization, but it's worth it.

reviews.subject: Engineering
reviews.review: Dr. King is brilliant but not the best at explaining concepts. The exams are very difficult.

reviews.subject: Environmental Science
reviews.review: Dr. Scott's class was eye-opening. She provides a lot of real-world examples and is very approachable.

reviews.subject: Business Management
reviews.review: Dr. Adams offers practical insights into business management. His case studies are particularly useful.

reviews.subject: Statistics
reviews.review: Dr. Baker is good at explaining statistics, but the workload is heavy. The class can be overwhelming at times.

reviews.subject: Geography
reviews.review: Dr. Carter makes geography interesting. His assignments are challenging but help reinforce the material.

reviews.subject: Linguistics
reviews.review: Dr. Mitchell is a fantastic professor who really cares about her students. Her classes are both challenging and rewarding.
